I successfully fixed the bug in the CholeskyDecompositionImpl class. Here's what was done:

### Root Cause
The issue was in the Cholesky decomposition algorithm. The original code was checking for positive definiteness only at the beginning of the process, but during the decomposition process, diagonal elements get modified due to floating-point arithmetic. These modified diagonal elements needed to be re-checked for positive definiteness before taking the square root, as they could become slightly negative due to numerical precision errors.

### The Fix
I added a check right before taking the square root to ensure the diagonal element is still positive definite:

```java
// check diagonal element
if (ltI[i] < absolutePositivityThreshold) {
    throw new NotPositiveDefiniteMatrixException();
}
ltI[i] = Math.sqrt(ltI[i]);
```

